Provides a configuration for the syslog-ng system.

@author Gunnar Wrobel <p@rdus.de>
@version 1.0
@package service_syslog

@module os_gentoo     The os_gentoo module is required for Gentoo support.

@fact operatingsystem Allows to choose the correct actions depending
                      on the operating system

@param service_syslog_remote_ip     If the syslog entries should be sent to a
                                    remote IP this should hold the IP address
                                    (Default: false)
@param service_syslog_remote_port   If the syslog entries should be sent to a
                                    remote IP this should hold the remote port
                                    (Default: 514)
@param service_syslog_accept_remote If the daemon should accept remote syslog
                                    entries this should be set to true.
                                    (Default: false)
@param run_services                 Determines if the syslog service should be
                                    started. (Default: true)
